### CSS Flexbox

**Flexbox** is a one-dimensional layout model for distributing space along a row or column.

---

### What is Flexbox?

```css
.container {
  display: flex;
}
```

Flexbox makes items:
- Align horizontally or vertically easily
- Reorder without changing HTML
- Fill available space automatically
- Center with one line

---

### Flexbox Terminology

```
    [Main Axis] (horizontal by default)
    +-------+-------+-------+
    | Item  | Item  | Item  |
    +-------+-------+-------+
    [Cross Axis] (vertical)
```

| Term | Description |
|------|-------------|
| **Flex Container** | Parent with `display: flex` |
| **Flex Items** | Direct children of container |
| **Main Axis** | Primary direction (row or column) |
| **Cross Axis** | Perpendicular to main axis |

---

### Container vs Item Properties

**Container properties:**
```css
.container {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: row;
  flex-wrap: wrap;
  justify-content: center;
  align-items: center;
  gap: 10px;
}
```

**Item properties:**
```css
.item {
  flex-grow: 1;
  flex-shrink: 0;
  flex-basis: 200px;
  align-self: center;
  order: 0;
}
```

---

### Quick Example

```css
.container {
  display: flex;
  justify-content: space-between;
}

.item {
  flex: 1;
  padding: 20px;
}
```

Three items with equal width, spaced evenly.

---

### Browser Support

Flexbox is supported in **all modern browsers** (IE 11+).

> **Key Point:** Flexbox is **one-dimensional** (row OR column). For two-dimensional layout, use CSS Grid.
